  "description": {
    "en": "The primary bioactive curcuminoid in turmeric, responsible for its bright yellow color. A diarylheptanoid with potent anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and chemopreventive properties. One of the most studied natural compounds.",
    "zh-Hant": "薑黃中的主要生物活性薑黃素類化合物，負責其鮮豔的黃色。一種二芳基庚烷，具有強效的抗炎、抗氧化和化學預防特性。研究最多的天然化合物之一。"
  },
  "foundIn": [
    {
      "@id": "https://www.herbapedia.org/entity/botanical/species/turmeric"
    }
  ],
  "pharmacology": [
    "Anti-inflammatory (via NF-κB inhibition)",
    "Antioxidant (scavenges free radicals)",
    "Chemopreventive activity",
    "Hepatoprotective effects",
    "Neuroprotective effects",
    "Antimicrobial activity"
  ],
  "bioavailability": {
    "en": "Very poor oral bioavailability due to low absorption, rapid metabolism, and elimination. Enhanced by piperine (black pepper) or lipid formulations."
  },
  "safetyData": {
    "ld50": "Oral, mouse: > 2 g/kg",
    "toxicity": "Generally Recognized As Safe (GRAS) by FDA",
    "warnings": [
      "High doses may cause gastrointestinal upset",
      "May interact with anticoagulants",
      "Gallbladder contraction risk"
    ]
  },
